description.narrative: In total, 640,810 diarrhoea cases (95%) and 721,817 pneumonia cases (95%) were treated in 128 health zones (HZs). In 2019, 1,520,00 children under-five years received 2,315,341 IMCI kits with treatment for diarrhoea and 177,572 pregnant women received delivery kits for safe childbirths in 48 HZs. The clinical mentorship program is improving mentees' performance across emergency obstetric and neonatal care. From January to June 2019, some changes have been shown in key birth outcomes such as the effective coverage of oxytocin injections increasing from 56 % to 81% and the percentage of newborns under hypothermia management increasing from 9% to 34%. | Status:Met | As-of Date:07/02/2020
